title: Pseudotsuga menziesii - Douglas fir
description: Mature Douglas fir forming a fairly closed canopy and bordering mountain big sagebrush steppe at the southwest end of the Spanish Peaks near Jack Creek Road, Madison Range, Madison County, Montana. The mature Douglas fir forest here forms a distinct environment because of the distinction of the plant composition of the forest understory, which is exemplified by an abundance of fairly well developed shrubs of Vaccinium globulare, common huckleberry.
label: Original
